{{Quote|The Sith Lord may have played me for a ''fool'' as you say-- but along with my brother and your young Rebel-- he's ''doomed'' himself! There's no way to bring aid into the crystal forest... or for him to get ''out''!|Domina Tagge|<ref name="Star Wars (1977) 37">[[Star Wars (1977) 37|''Star Wars'' (1977) 37]]</ref>}}
The '''Crystal Valley''' was an area on the planet [[Monastery/Legends|Monastery]] where large [[Crystal/Legends|crystal]] spires would grow from the ground at dangerous speeds. The valley was to be the site where [[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] and [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] had a [[Lightsaber/Legends|lightsaber]] duel, and was chosen by [[Domina Tagge/Legends|Domina Tagge]] because she wanted to ensure that both combatants were killed. However, Vader substituted [[Baron/Legends|Baron]] [[Orman Tagge/Legends|Orman Tagge]] in place of himself possibly using [[Mind trick/Legends|Force Illusion]], and Luke killed the Baron before escaping the Valley.

